comments: CFD - This assumes all courses in PROGRAM_COURSE are mandatory.

CFD - This lists all of the math courses that appear in PROGRAM_COURSE. Currently, these are all courses that happen to be required by the major. However, what happens if an ULCS course or something like that is cross-listed in the math department?

sentence-with-vars: What are the department0 classes I have to take to graduate as a CS major ?
sql: SELECT DISTINCT COURSEalias0.DEPARTMENT , COURSEalias0.NAME , COURSEalias0.NUMBER FROM PROGRAM_COURSE AS PROGRAM_COURSEalias0 INNER JOIN COURSE AS COURSEalias0 ON PROGRAM_COURSEalias0.COURSE_ID = COURSEalias0.COURSE_ID WHERE COURSEalias0.DEPARTMENT = "MATH" ;
